│ Understanding the Issue:\nThe crash occurs in                                 │
│ BoUpSLP::removeInstructionsAndOperands during horizontal reduction            │
│ vectorization. The assertion checks that each instruction being erased either │
│ has no users or all its users are already marked deleted. In the reproducer,  │
│ scalar compare instructions (%cmp80... and %tobool...) are scheduled for      │
│ deletion while they are still used by a chain of select instructions          │
│ implementing a boolean reduction. Those select instructions are part of the   │
│ reduction but are kept temporarily (they are placed in UserIgnoreList). The   │
│ validation code earlier (vectorizeTree) explicitly allows erasing scalars     │
│ whose users are in UserIgnoreList, but removeInstructionsAndOperands'         │
│ assertion does not account for this case. As a result, the assertion fires    │
│ even though the situation is intended and handled elsewhere.\n\n2. Analyzing  │
│ opt's Log:\nThe debug log shows lines such as:\nSLP: \\tvalidating user:      │
│ %cmp80.1.2.i.i = select ...\nSLP: \\tErasing scalar:  %cmp80.1.2.i.i193 =     │
